Sentencas: Fe-, Ni- and Zn- doped La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 are prepared and a single-component solid oxide fuel cell composed of 30 wt% perovskite oxide and 70 wt% samarium-doped ceria (SDC)-(Li0.67Na0.33)(2)CO3 is fabricated and characterized.
Titulo: Effect of Fe, Ni and Zn dopants in La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 on the electrochemical performance of single-component solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: When doping with either Fe, Ni or Zn, most cations occupy the Co3+ sites.
Titulo: Effect of Fe, Ni and Zn dopants in La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 on the electrochemical performance of single-component solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy and oxygen temperature-programmed desorption characterizations show that Zn-doped La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 exhibits notably high surface oxygen, causing higher catalytic activity for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) than that of nondoped La0.9Sr0.1CoO3.
Titulo: Effect of Fe, Ni and Zn dopants in La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 on the electrochemical performance of single-component solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Fe or Ni doping into La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 decreases surface oxygen, resulting in a lower catalytic activity toward ORR than La0.9Sr0.1CoO3.
Titulo: Effect of Fe, Ni and Zn dopants in La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 on the electrochemical performance of single-component solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Furthermore, X-ray diffraction, temperature-programmed reduction and transmission electron microscopy characterizations prove that after reduction, Fe-doped La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 is reduced to Co0.72Fe0.28 alloy-oxide core-shell nanoparticles, resulting in a high catalytic activity for hydrogen oxygen reaction (HOR).
Titulo: Effect of Fe, Ni and Zn dopants in La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 on the electrochemical performance of single-component solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: However, NiCo2O4 are formed during the reduction of Ni-doped La0.9Sr0.1CoO3, exhibiting a low catalytic activity for the HOR.
Titulo: Effect of Fe, Ni and Zn dopants in La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 on the electrochemical performance of single-component solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Similarly, the low catalytic activity of reduced Zn-doped La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 for the HOR is caused by the formation of ZnCo2O4.
Titulo: Effect of Fe, Ni and Zn dopants in La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 on the electrochemical performance of single-component solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: A single component fuel cell composed with Fe-doped La0.9Sr0.1CoO3-SDC-(Li0.62Na0.33)(2)CO3 exhibits the highest P-max of 239.1 mW Cm-2 at 700 degrees C with H-2 as fuel, indicating that HOR processes are rate-determining steps.
Titulo: Effect of Fe, Ni and Zn dopants in La0.9Sr0.1CoO3 on the electrochemical performance of single-component solid oxide fuel cell
